{"markdown":{"yaml":{"title":""},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"page-container\">\n  <div class=\"project-page\">\n\n    <a href=\"../index.html#projects\" class=\"back-link\">\n      <i class=\"ti ti-arrow-left\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Back to projects\n    </a>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-header\">\n      <div class=\"proj-tags\">\n        <span class=\"proj-tag tag-blue\">Capstone Project</span>\n        <span class=\"proj-tag tag-amber\">Descriptive Statistics · Trend Analysis</span>\n        <span class=\"proj-tag tag-gray\">Higher Ed · Program Evaluation</span>\n        <span class=\"proj-tag tag-teal\">R · Tableau · Quarto</span>\n      </div>\n      <h1 class=\"proj-title\">Student Enrollment Patterns in a Public Affairs Graduate Program: A 10-Year Trend Analysis</h1>\n      <p class=\"proj-desc\">Analysis of 10 years of student enrollment records across UIC's MPA, MPP, and MSCA programs — examining course sequencing, course load, time to degree, and shifting subject preferences. Presented to the PPMA department.</p>\n      <div class=\"collab-note\">\n        <i class=\"ti ti-users\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>\n        <span>Co-authored with Ronnie Chen and Imaan Jahangir. My contributions: data cleaning, reproducible Quarto report, visualizations, and Q1 (course sequencing), Q3 (time to degree), and Q7 (course retakes) analyses.</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-actions\">\n      <a href=\"02_Report_PPMA.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"btn-primary\">\n        <i class=\"ti ti-file-text\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Read Full Report\n      </a>\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/Haedodam/Student-Enrollment-Patterns\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"btn-outline\">\n        <i class=\"ti ti-brand-github\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> View Code\n      </a>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-meta\">\n      <div class=\"meta-item\">\n        <p class=\"meta-label\">Year</p>\n        <p class=\"meta-val\">2026</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"meta-item\">\n        <p class=\"meta-label\">Type</p>\n        <p class=\"meta-val\">Capstone Project</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"meta-item\">\n        <p class=\"meta-label\">Course</p>\n        <p class=\"meta-val\">PA590</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"meta-item\">\n        <p class=\"meta-label\">Tools</p>\n        <p class=\"meta-val\">R · Tableau · Quarto</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-stats\">\n      <div class=\"stat-card\">\n        <p class=\"stat-num stat-teal\">2015–2025</p>\n        <p class=\"stat-label\">academic years covered</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"stat-card\">\n        <p class=\"stat-num stat-blue\">3</p>\n        <p class=\"stat-label\">graduate programs analyzed (MPA, MPP, MSCA)</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"stat-card\">\n        <p class=\"stat-num stat-amber\">7</p>\n        <p class=\"stat-label\">research questions examined</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-section\">\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Research questions</h2>\n      <div class=\"q-grid\">\n        <div class=\"q-card\"><span class=\"q-num\">Q1</span><p class=\"q-text\">Are students following the recommended course sequence?</p></div>\n        <div class=\"q-card\"><span class=\"q-num\">Q2</span><p class=\"q-text\">Are there signs of course overload?</p></div>\n        <div class=\"q-card\"><span class=\"q-num\">Q3</span><p class=\"q-text\">How has time to degree changed over time?</p></div>\n        <div class=\"q-card\"><span class=\"q-num\">Q4</span><p class=\"q-text\">How have enrollment patterns across concentrations shifted?</p></div>\n        <div class=\"q-card\"><span class=\"q-num\">Q5</span><p class=\"q-text\">How much do students deviate from the recommended course plan?</p></div>\n        <div class=\"q-card\"><span class=\"q-num\">Q6</span><p class=\"q-text\">How has participation in nonprofit coursework changed?</p></div>\n        <div class=\"q-card\"><span class=\"q-num\">Q7</span><p class=\"q-text\">To what extent do students retake courses?</p></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-section\">\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Visualizations</h2>\n      <div style=\"margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\">\n        <img src=\"fig1.png\" alt=\"Timing of Core Course Enrollment\" style=\"width:100%; border: 0.5px solid #e5e5e5; border-radius: 8px;\">\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <img src=\"fig10.png\" alt=\"Most Frequently Retaken Courses\" style=\"width:100%; border: 0.5px solid #e5e5e5; border-radius: 8px;\">\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-section\">\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Key findings</h2>\n      <ul class=\"finding-list\">\n        <li class=\"finding-item\">\n          <div class=\"finding-icon fi-teal\">\n            <i class=\"ti ti-route\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"finding-text\"><strong>Students largely follow the intended curriculum structure.</strong> Most complete foundational courses within their first two available opportunities, with timing variation driven by course scheduling rather than intentional deviation.</p>\n        </li>\n        <li class=\"finding-item\">\n          <div class=\"finding-icon fi-blue\">\n            <i class=\"ti ti-clock\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"finding-text\"><strong>Time to degree is stable and aligned with program expectations.</strong> Most students complete within 2.5–3 years. Recent cohorts show both faster and more consistent completion, with 86% of 2024–2025 graduates finishing within 3 years.</p>\n        </li>\n        <li class=\"finding-item\">\n          <div class=\"finding-icon fi-amber\">\n            <i class=\"ti ti-trending-up\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"finding-text\"><strong>Demand for data and analytics coursework is growing.</strong> Enrollments in methods and analytics courses have increased steadily, while nonprofit and governance courses remain stable but lower in participation.</p>\n        </li>\n        <li class=\"finding-item\">\n          <div class=\"finding-icon fi-gray\">\n            <i class=\"ti ti-repeat\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"finding-text\"><strong>Course retakes are uncommon and concentrated.</strong> Only 15.7% of students retook any course, with retakes concentrated in a small number of foundational courses (PA 504, PA 506, PA 401).</p>\n        </li>\n      </ul>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-section\">\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Post-presentation analysis</h2>\n      <p class=\"body-text\">Following the final presentation, additional analysis was conducted in response to feedback from the client meeting. The findings reveal a connection between course sequencing, overload, and retake likelihood.</p>\n      <ul class=\"finding-list\">\n        <li class=\"finding-item\">\n          <div class=\"finding-icon fi-blue\">\n            <i class=\"ti ti-books\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"finding-text\"><strong>Students who retake courses carry significantly higher course loads.</strong> Retake students average 15.22 credits per term vs. 10.79 for non-retake students, and take more courses per term (3.86 vs. 2.74).</p>\n        </li>\n        <li class=\"finding-item\">\n          <div class=\"finding-icon fi-amber\">\n            <i class=\"ti ti-alert-triangle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"finding-text\"><strong>66.7% of retaken courses were first taken under overload conditions</strong> (more than 12 credits), with a mean credit load of 15.75 at first attempt.</p>\n        </li>\n        <li class=\"finding-item\">\n          <div class=\"finding-icon fi-teal\">\n            <i class=\"ti ti-arrow-right\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i>\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"finding-text\"><strong>Taking PA 504 before PA 403 increases the likelihood of retaking PA 504.</strong> Students who took PA 504 before PA 403 retook it at 2.5%, compared to 0.6% for those who followed the recommended sequence — 4× higher.</p>\n        </li>\n      </ul>\n      <div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.25rem;\">\n  <img src=\"table_1_retake_load_comparison.png\" alt=\"Table 1: Retake and course load comparison\" style=\"width:100%; border: 0.5px solid #e5e5e5; border-radius: 8px;\">\n  <img src=\"table_3_pa504_order_vs_retake.png\" alt=\"Table 3: PA 504 order vs retake likelihood\" style=\"width:100%; border: 0.5px solid #e5e5e5; border-radius: 8px;\">\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-section\">\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Implications</h2>\n      <p class=\"body-text\">The findings suggest that student progression is shaped more by program design and course availability than by individual student behavior. Expanding high-demand sections in analytics and finance, and more intentional course scheduling, could reduce overload and better align availability with student demand.</p>\n      <div class=\"highlight-box\">Structural factors — course availability and program design — are the primary drivers of how students navigate the curriculum.</div>\n    </div>\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n```","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"page-container\">\n  <div class=\"project-page\">\n\n    <a href=\"../index.html#projects\" class=\"back-link\">\n      <i class=\"ti ti-arrow-left\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Back to projects\n    </a>\n\n    <div class=\"proj-header\">\n      <div class=\"proj-tags\">\n        <span class=\"proj-tag tag-blue\">Capstone Project</span>\n        <span class=\"proj-tag tag-amber\">Descriptive Statistics · Trend Analysis</span>\n        <span class=\"proj-tag tag-gray\">Higher Ed · Program Evaluation</span>\n        <span class=\"proj-tag tag-teal\">R · Tableau · Quarto</span>\